  "description": "Single storey rear extension with internal alterations.",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development would not respect the historic building lines of the building and combined with its lack of fenestration and articulation, appear incongruous and have a detrimental impact upon the architectural interest and significance of a non-designated heritage asset and fail to make a positive contribution to local character and distinctiveness. As such, the proposal is contrary to Policy DC67 of the London Borough of Havering Local Development Framework Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document 2008 and the London Borough of Havering Heritage Supplementary Planning Document Adopted April 2011. Further, the proposal is considered contrary to guidance contained within paragraph 197 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2019.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given to Intelliarch Ltd via email on 4th March 2021."
